  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A UQ campaign was conducted examining inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity; Sobol indices were computed and documented in the validation report, confirming that rotational speed accounts for 62% of hemolysis index variance. Sensitivity findings are discussed in ValidationResult vr-uq-sobol and inform the acceptance rationale.",
