      "name": "Mesh convergence study — discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level structured mesh refinement (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M cells). GCI-based discretization uncertainty estimated at 4.2% for nIH at worst-case operating point. Asymptotic convergence confirmed (GCI ratio 1.02)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-uq-sobol",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "UQ campaign — Sobol sensitivity indices for hemolysis QoI",
      "description": "A 512-sample quasi-Monte Carlo UQ campaign was executed varying inlet flow rate (±15%), rotational speed (±10%), and blood viscosity (±8%). First-order and total-order Sobol indices computed via the Saltelli estimator. Rotational speed dominates hemolysis index variance (S1=0.62, ST=0.71); inlet flow contributes S1=0.24. Viscosity interaction effects are minor (ST=0.09). These findings confirm the adequacy of the 5 flow-speed test matrix and support the acceptance decision. Full Sobol index tables are archived in dataset uq-sobol-sample-matrix."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-code-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Code verification — method of manufactured solutions",
      "description": "MMS verification of the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver confirms second-order spatial convergence. Power-law hemolysis transport equation verified against analytical solution; L2 error norm reduces at expected rate across three refinement levels."
    }
